<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="21" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="21">
If these specimens are conspecific, the species would have a Gulf of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="México-Atlantic">Mexico-Atlantic</normalizedToken>
and Eastern Pacific distribution, which is untenable, for the following reasons. A strong genetic discontinuity between Gulf and Atlantic populations has been noted for specimens living in Florida (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-294X.2006.03061.x" author="Soltis, DE" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Ecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" pagination="4261 - 4293" refId="B52" refString="Soltis, DE, Morris, AB, McLachlan, JS, Manos, PS, Soltis, PS, 2006. Comparative phylogeography of unglaciated eastern North America. Molecular Ecology 15: 4261 - 4293" title="Comparative phylogeography of unglaciated eastern North America." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-294X.2006.03061.x" volume="15" year="2006">Soltis et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0203644" author="Bijak, AL" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" refId="B2" refString="Bijak, AL, van Dijk, K, Waycott, M, 2018. .https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0203644" url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0203644" year="2018">Bijak et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
), and amphi-American species have been progressively recognized as including more than one distinct species upon morphological features and genetic markers combined (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2880.1.5" author="Carrera-Parra, LF" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" pagination="51 - 64" refId="B5" refString="Carrera-Parra, LF, Salazar-Vallejo, SI, 2011. Redescriptions of Eunicefilamentosa and E.denticulata and description of E.tovarae n. sp. (Polychaeta: Eunicidae) highlighted with morphological and molecular data. Zootaxa 2880: 51 - 64" title="Redescriptions of Eunicefilamentosa and E. denticulata and description of E. tovarae n. sp. (Polychaeta: Eunicidae) highlighted with morphological and molecular data." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2880.1.5" volume="2880" year="2011">Carrera-Parra and Salazar-Vallejo 2011</bibRefCitation>
), or even after the analysis of morphological differences (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.518.9564" author="Conde-Vela, VM" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" pagination="15 - 49" refId="B8" refString="Conde-Vela, VM, Salazar-Vallejo, SI, 2015. Redescriptions of Nereisoligohalina (Rioja, 1946) and N.garwoodi Gonzalez-Escalante &amp; Salazar-Vallejo, 2003 and description of N.confusa sp. n. (Annelida, Nereididae). ZooKeys 518: 15 - 49" title="Redescriptions of Nereisoligohalina (Rioja, 1946) and N. garwoodi Gonzalez-Escalante &amp; Salazar-Vallejo, 2003 and description of N. confusa sp. n. (Annelida, Nereididae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.518.9564" volume="518" year="2015">Conde-Vela and Salazar-Vallejo 2015</bibRefCitation>
). Consequently, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. bassi" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" rank="species" species="bassi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">S. bassi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be regarded as a northwestern Atlantic species restricted to the Gulf of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="México">Mexico</normalizedToken>
; new names and descriptions will be provided for the specimens from Beaufort, NC, and Los Angeles, California in a subsequent publication. Chances are, however, that the same species might extend from the Gulf of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="México">Mexico</normalizedToken>
to Beaufort, NC On the other hand, it should be noted that specimens from San Francisco have been regarded as belonging to a different species since 2013 (
<bibRefCitation author="Norris, D" journalOrPublisher="Oceanside Biology Laboratory Voucher Sheet, City and County of San Francisco" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" refId="B44" refString="Norris, D, 2013. Sigambra sp. SF1. Oceanside Biology Laboratory Voucher Sheet, City and County of San Francisco" title="Sigambra sp. SF 1." year="2013">Norris 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
